{
  "video_id": "ztninkgZ0ws",
  "title": "Is an Ice Age Coming? | Space Time | PBS Digital Studios",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 3050.0,
      "end_time": 6030.0,
      "text": "Earth's climate shifts\nbetween short periods"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 6030.0,
      "end_time": 9870.0,
      "text": "of warm and long, long\nperiods of frigid cold."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 9870.0,
      "end_time": 11960.0,
      "text": "Based on past pans,\nthere's reason"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 11960.0,
      "end_time": 15720.0,
      "text": "to think that the current warm\nperiod might be nearly done."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 15720.0,
      "end_time": 19540.0,
      "text": "Is the Ice Age coming back,\nor will human activity"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 19540.0,
      "end_time": 21756.0,
      "text": "swing us wildly in the\nopposite direction?"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 27690.0,
      "end_time": 30140.0,
      "text": "We live in an ice age."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 30140.0,
      "end_time": 32920.0,
      "text": "Our geological period\nis the Quaternary,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 32920.0,
      "end_time": 36980.0,
      "text": "and is characterized by a\nmassive glaciation-- vast ice"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36980.0,
      "end_time": 39310.0,
      "text": "sheets stretching\nfrom the Arctic"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39310.0,
      "end_time": 43030.0,
      "text": "all the way down to the Missouri\nRiver through Siberia, much"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 43030.0,
      "end_time": 47330.0,
      "text": "of Europe, and spreading out\nfrom all major mountain ranges."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 47330.0,
      "end_time": 48870.0,
      "text": "OK, sure."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 48870.0,
      "end_time": 52299.0,
      "text": "Right now, we're in a\nbrief interglacial phase--"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 52299.0,
      "end_time": 53840.0,
      "text": "a relatively summery\nstretch in which"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53840.0,
      "end_time": 56650.0,
      "text": "the glaciers have retreated."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56650.0,
      "end_time": 59910.0,
      "text": "These interglacial\nperiods are short lived."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 59910.0,
      "end_time": 63400.0,
      "text": "The Quaternary Ice Age has\nlasted 2.5 million years"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63400.0,
      "end_time": 64550.0,
      "text": "so far."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 64550.0,
      "end_time": 68450.0,
      "text": "It's 10,000 to 15,000-year\nwarm patches are separated"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 68450.0,
      "end_time": 72330.0,
      "text": "by glacial periods that last\nseveral times as long as."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 72330.0,
      "end_time": 75730.0,
      "text": "The current respite is\ncalled the Holocene era,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 75730.0,
      "end_time": 78070.0,
      "text": "and it began around\n11,000 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 78070.0,
      "end_time": 82500.0,
      "text": "Temperatures rose, glaciers, and\nwoolly mammoths migrated north,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 82500.0,
      "end_time": 84850.0,
      "text": "and humans thrived."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 84850.0,
      "end_time": 87540.0,
      "text": "This new era of\nwarmth and plenty"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 87540.0,
      "end_time": 91210.0,
      "text": "saw the rise of agriculture,\nwriting, cities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 91210.0,
      "end_time": 93020.0,
      "text": "and technology."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 93020.0,
      "end_time": 96705.0,
      "text": "All of our recorded, even\nour remembered history,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 96705.0,
      "end_time": 98540.0,
      "text": "is of the Holocene."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 98540.0,
      "end_time": 100130.0,
      "text": "You might forgive\nus for imagining"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 100130.0,
      "end_time": 102860.0,
      "text": "that these relatively\nsummery millennia are"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 102860.0,
      "end_time": 105010.0,
      "text": "normal for this planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 105010.0,
      "end_time": 106960.0,
      "text": "That is not the case."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 106960.0,
      "end_time": 109660.0,
      "text": "The current interglacial\nis already long."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 109660.0,
      "end_time": 112824.0,
      "text": "Does this mean that the\nglaciers are overdue?"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 112824.0,
      "end_time": 114910.0,
      "text": "Is winter coming?"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 114910.0,
      "end_time": 116800.0,
      "text": "To answer these\nquestions, we need"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 116800.0,
      "end_time": 120310.0,
      "text": "to understand what triggers\nthe march of the glaciers"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 120310.0,
      "end_time": 122540.0,
      "text": "and why they eventually retreat."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 122540.0,
      "end_time": 125230.0,
      "text": "In fact, we know the\nbroad answer to this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 125230.0,
      "end_time": 127900.0,
      "text": "even if the details\nare under debate."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 127900.0,
      "end_time": 131350.0,
      "text": "Earth's motion around the\nsun changes, and with it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 131350.0,
      "end_time": 134290.0,
      "text": "the intensity and\ndistribution of sunlight."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 134290.0,
      "end_time": 137190.0,
      "text": "It was Serbian scientist\nMilutin Milankovitch"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 137190.0,
      "end_time": 140190.0,
      "text": "who realized that the\ngravitational tug of Jupiter"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 140190.0,
      "end_time": 143910.0,
      "text": "and Saturn would lead to\nthree periodic shifts that"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 143910.0,
      "end_time": 148020.0,
      "text": "might explain the\nenormous climatic swings"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 148020.0,
      "end_time": 150050.0,
      "text": "of the Quaternary period."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 150050.0,
      "end_time": 152530.0,
      "text": "These are the\nMilankovitch cycles."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 152530.0,
      "end_time": 153950.0,
      "text": "Let me summarize."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 153950.0,
      "end_time": 157640.0,
      "text": "One-- the elongation\nor the eccentricity"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 157640.0,
      "end_time": 161250.0,
      "text": "of Earth's elliptical orbit\nshifts from almost completely"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 161250.0,
      "end_time": 165000.0,
      "text": "circular to somewhat more\nelliptical in 100,000-years"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 165000.0,
      "end_time": 166190.0,
      "text": "cycle."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 166190.0,
      "end_time": 168790.0,
      "text": "At the absolute\nmaximum eccentricity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 168790.0,
      "end_time": 171150.0,
      "text": "Earth's most distant\npoint from the sun--"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 171150.0,
      "end_time": 175130.0,
      "text": "the Aphelion-- is\nabout 30% further"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 175130.0,
      "end_time": 178530.0,
      "text": "than the closest\npoint, the Perihelion."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 178530.0,
      "end_time": 183500.0,
      "text": "One hemisphere will experience\nsummer at Aphelion and winter"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 183500.0,
      "end_time": 188440.0,
      "text": "at Perihelion and milder\nseasons all around."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 188440.0,
      "end_time": 190950.0,
      "text": "That's the north at the moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 190950.0,
      "end_time": 194090.0,
      "text": "The Southern Hemisphere is\ncloser to the sun in summer"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 194090.0,
      "end_time": 198150.0,
      "text": "and further in the winter,\nso more extreme seasons."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 198150.0,
      "end_time": 200320.0,
      "text": "However, the difference\nin sunlight intensity"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 200320.0,
      "end_time": 203350.0,
      "text": "due to this difference\nin distance from the sun"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 203350.0,
      "end_time": 206850.0,
      "text": "is much less than\nthe simple difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 206850.0,
      "end_time": 209040.0,
      "text": "due to the seasons themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 209040.0,
      "end_time": 211700.0,
      "text": "So this shouldn't\nbe a huge effect."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 211700.0,
      "end_time": 215580.0,
      "text": "Two, the pointing of\nEarth's axis precesses."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 215580.0,
      "end_time": 221960.0,
      "text": "It rotates 360 degrees over\napproximately 26,000 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 221960.0,
      "end_time": 225540.0,
      "text": "In addition, the long axis\nof Earth's elliptical orbit"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 225540.0,
      "end_time": 227260.0,
      "text": "also precesses."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 227260.0,
      "end_time": 231030.0,
      "text": "Together, these two effects\ndefine where in the orbit"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 231030.0,
      "end_time": 232650.0,
      "text": "the seasons occur."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 232650.0,
      "end_time": 237060.0,
      "text": "They combine to produce a\n21,000-year cycle called"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 237060.0,
      "end_time": 239620.0,
      "text": "the precession of the equinoxes."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 239620.0,
      "end_time": 243990.0,
      "text": "So eventually, the north's\nmild Perihelion winter"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 243990.0,
      "end_time": 247800.0,
      "text": "will turn into a\ncold Aphelion winter."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 247800.0,
      "end_time": 251590.0,
      "text": "And 3- Earth's tilt changes."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 251590.0,
      "end_time": 256310.0,
      "text": "Our spin axis is now tilted\nat 23 1/2 degrees relative"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 256310.0,
      "end_time": 258000.0,
      "text": "to the axis of our orbit."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 258000.0,
      "end_time": 264140.0,
      "text": "This obliquity oscillates\nbetween 22.1 and 24.5 degrees"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 264140.0,
      "end_time": 266641.0,
      "text": "over 41,000 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 266641.0,
      "end_time": 270950.0,
      "text": "High obliquity means\nmore extreme seasons."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 270950.0,
      "end_time": 275890.0,
      "text": "But it's low obliquity that\nultimately leads to a colder"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 275890.0,
      "end_time": 277230.0,
      "text": "global climate climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 277230.0,
      "end_time": 281180.0,
      "text": "Because then the highest\nlatitudes, where glaciation"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 281180.0,
      "end_time": 283940.0,
      "text": "begins, never get much sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 283940.0,
      "end_time": 287250.0,
      "text": "Now, Milankovitch\npredicted that obliquity"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 287250.0,
      "end_time": 290340.0,
      "text": "would drive climate\nvariations, because it governs"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 290340.0,
      "end_time": 292700.0,
      "text": "the strength of the seasons."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 292700.0,
      "end_time": 294800.0,
      "text": "But how can we test this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 294800.0,
      "end_time": 296950.0,
      "text": "Paleoclimatology."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 296950.0,
      "end_time": 300260.0,
      "text": "We can reconstruct our\nplanet's climate history"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 300260.0,
      "end_time": 302780.0,
      "text": "by digging holes."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 302780.0,
      "end_time": 306030.0,
      "text": "First, glacial ice cores."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 306030.0,
      "end_time": 309320.0,
      "text": "The most famous is the nearly\nfour-kilometer-deep hole"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 309320.0,
      "end_time": 311940.0,
      "text": "drilled in the Vostok\nGlacier in Antarctica."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 311940.0,
      "end_time": 316370.0,
      "text": "This glacier was built up\nby millennia of snowfall."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 316370.0,
      "end_time": 319200.0,
      "text": "Each year's layer carries\nbubbles of the Earth's"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 319200.0,
      "end_time": 321940.0,
      "text": "atmosphere from that time."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 321940.0,
      "end_time": 325610.0,
      "text": "Isotope ratios and greenhouse\ngas content in those"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 325610.0,
      "end_time": 331810.0,
      "text": "bubbles traces global climate\nover the past 420,000 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 331810.0,
      "end_time": 336360.0,
      "text": "Second-- oceanic sediment\ncores reveal the changes"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 336360.0,
      "end_time": 340560.0,
      "text": "in ocean floor sea life,\nwhose composition also depends"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 340560.0,
      "end_time": 343220.0,
      "text": "sensitively on\nocean temperatures"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 343220.0,
      "end_time": 349080.0,
      "text": "and salinity, and so also on\nglobal climate and ice volume."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 349080.0,
      "end_time": 353010.0,
      "text": "Ocean cores get us a climate\nrecord back tens of millions"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 353010.0,
      "end_time": 354210.0,
      "text": "of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 354210.0,
      "end_time": 357550.0,
      "text": "If you look back to the early\nQuaternary-- earlier than, say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 357550.0,
      "end_time": 361460.0,
      "text": "a million years ago-- it\nseems Milankovitch was right."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 361460.0,
      "end_time": 364660.0,
      "text": "Temperature goes up and down\non the roughly 40,000-year time"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 364660.0,
      "end_time": 366950.0,
      "text": "scale of changing obliquity."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 366950.0,
      "end_time": 370880.0,
      "text": "But then, around 800,000\nto 900,000 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 370880.0,
      "end_time": 372620.0,
      "text": "something changed."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 372620.0,
      "end_time": 375930.0,
      "text": "As Earth reached the depth\nof the current ice age,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 375930.0,
      "end_time": 377650.0,
      "text": "the cycle shifted."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 377650.0,
      "end_time": 382240.0,
      "text": "Now the warm periods come\nonly once every 100,000 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 382240.0,
      "end_time": 386760.0,
      "text": "They seem to follow the change\nin eccentricity, not obliquity."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 386760.0,
      "end_time": 391790.0,
      "text": "Every time Earth's orbit becomes\nmore circular, the planet warms"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 391790.0,
      "end_time": 393740.0,
      "text": "and the glaciers go away."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 393740.0,
      "end_time": 397410.0,
      "text": "As eccentricity increases\nagain, the glaciers return."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 397410.0,
      "end_time": 400350.0,
      "text": "This is totally weird,\nbecause eccentricity"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 400350.0,
      "end_time": 403750.0,
      "text": "should produce a much smaller\neffect than obliquity."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 403750.0,
      "end_time": 405630.0,
      "text": "So what changed?"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 405630.0,
      "end_time": 407680.0,
      "text": "It's not entirely clear."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 407680.0,
      "end_time": 411010.0,
      "text": "But it may be that we're\nnow so deep in the ice age"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 411010.0,
      "end_time": 413170.0,
      "text": "that it takes all of\nthe Milankovitch cycles"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 413170.0,
      "end_time": 416720.0,
      "text": "together to cause the\nglaciers to retreat."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 416720.0,
      "end_time": 420200.0,
      "text": "Eccentricity and\nobliquity and precession"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 420200.0,
      "end_time": 422290.0,
      "text": "must line up perfectly."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 422290.0,
      "end_time": 425220.0,
      "text": "The eccentricity\ncycle is the longest,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 425220.0,
      "end_time": 428300.0,
      "text": "and so the shifts\ncorrespond to its period."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 428300.0,
      "end_time": 428800.0,
      "text": "OK."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 428800.0,
      "end_time": 432960.0,
      "text": "So we're now in a warm interlude\nin the depth of an ice age."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 432960.0,
      "end_time": 436070.0,
      "text": "You might be wondering, when are\nthe glaciers going to rush down"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 436070.0,
      "end_time": 440850.0,
      "text": "from the north, bringing polar\nbears, white walkers, Tontons?"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 440850.0,
      "end_time": 442770.0,
      "text": "One thing is for\nsure-- the glaciers"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 442770.0,
      "end_time": 444250.0,
      "text": "will come from the north."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 444250.0,
      "end_time": 446240.0,
      "text": "The vast oceans of the\nSouthern Hemisphere"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 446240.0,
      "end_time": 449370.0,
      "text": "provide a powerful buffer\nagainst changes in temperature."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 449370.0,
      "end_time": 452300.0,
      "text": "Ice struggles to\nbuild up on water."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 452300.0,
      "end_time": 457140.0,
      "text": "But even now, northern winters\nsee ice and snow cover the land"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 457140.0,
      "end_time": 459420.0,
      "text": "all the way down to the\ncontinental US, Europe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 459420.0,
      "end_time": 460660.0,
      "text": "and China."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 460660.0,
      "end_time": 463800.0,
      "text": "In summer, it\nretreats completely."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 463800.0,
      "end_time": 466280.0,
      "text": "But if the climate were\na little bit cooler,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 466280.0,
      "end_time": 468480.0,
      "text": "then summer may\nnot be warm enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 468480.0,
      "end_time": 470800.0,
      "text": "to melt all of the winter snow."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 470800.0,
      "end_time": 473790.0,
      "text": "Then it would build\nup year after year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 473790.0,
      "end_time": 475860.0,
      "text": "slowly creeping south."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 475860.0,
      "end_time": 478750.0,
      "text": "Now, by themselves,\nshifts in Earth's orbit"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 478750.0,
      "end_time": 482010.0,
      "text": "aren't enough to\nradically change climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 482010.0,
      "end_time": 485930.0,
      "text": "But they are enough to trigger\npositive feedback cycles."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 485930.0,
      "end_time": 488100.0,
      "text": "As ice cover\nincreases, Earth starts"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 488100.0,
      "end_time": 490970.0,
      "text": "to reflect more\nincoming sunlight."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 490970.0,
      "end_time": 493270.0,
      "text": "Its albedo increases."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 493270.0,
      "end_time": 496110.0,
      "text": "More ice means less\nabsorbed sunlight,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 496110.0,
      "end_time": 500110.0,
      "text": "lowering global temperature and\nallowing even more ice to grow."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 500110.0,
      "end_time": 503890.0,
      "text": "The glaciation initiated\nby the Milankovitch cycles"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 503890.0,
      "end_time": 505510.0,
      "text": "accelerates."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 505510.0,
      "end_time": 508560.0,
      "text": "A second feedback cycle\nis equally important."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 508560.0,
      "end_time": 511940.0,
      "text": "Cooler oceans are better\nat absorbing carbon dioxide"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 511940.0,
      "end_time": 515140.0,
      "text": "from the atmosphere, and so\nthe Earth's natural greenhouse"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 515140.0,
      "end_time": 517130.0,
      "text": "effect is diminished."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 517130.0,
      "end_time": 519169.0,
      "text": "There is an\nunfortunate combination"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 519169.0,
      "end_time": 522809.0,
      "text": "of orbital properties that\nkickstarts this process."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 522808.99999999994,
      "end_time": 527810.0,
      "text": "First, low obliquity means less\noverall sun at high latitudes"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 527810.0,
      "end_time": 529840.0,
      "text": "where the glaciers start."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 529840.0,
      "end_time": 534670.0,
      "text": "Second, high eccentricity means\none hemisphere experiences"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 534670.0,
      "end_time": 539470.0,
      "text": "a bad winter at Aphelion,\nfurther from the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 539470.0,
      "end_time": 543430.0,
      "text": "Earth also moves slower at\nAphelion, and so those long,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 543430.0,
      "end_time": 545810.0,
      "text": "cold winters are\nnot counteracted"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 545810.0,
      "end_time": 548620.0,
      "text": "by the short, warmer summers."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 548620.0,
      "end_time": 552200.0,
      "text": "And third, the procession\nof the equinoxes"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 552200.0,
      "end_time": 555910.0,
      "text": "sends the glacier-prone\nNorthern Hemisphere"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 555910.0,
      "end_time": 560930.0,
      "text": "into a bitter Aphelion winter\nwhile the eccentricity is high."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 560930.0,
      "end_time": 563206.0,
      "text": "So when does this happen next?"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 563206.0,
      "end_time": 566850.0,
      "text": "Well, right now,\nobliquity is decreasing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 566850.0,
      "end_time": 570210.0,
      "text": "and it will bottom out\nin around 12,000 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 570210.0,
      "end_time": 573680.0,
      "text": "It's currently winter at\nPerihelion in the Northern"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 573680.0,
      "end_time": 576970.0,
      "text": "Hemisphere, but it'll\npersist completely"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 576970.0,
      "end_time": 580430.0,
      "text": "to the bad situation\nin 10,000 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 580430.0,
      "end_time": 585980.0,
      "text": "So over 10,000 to 12,000 years,\nall of that points to cooling."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 585980.0,
      "end_time": 589830.0,
      "text": "What about the 100,00-year\neccentricity cycle that seems"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 589830.0,
      "end_time": 592090.0,
      "text": "to define the overall cycle?"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 592090.0,
      "end_time": 594560.0,
      "text": "Well, actually,\nwe're just coming out"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 594560.0,
      "end_time": 596920.0,
      "text": "of a peak in eccentricity."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 596920.0,
      "end_time": 598456.0,
      "text": "That should've been bad."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 598456.0,
      "end_time": 600830.0,
      "text": "And perhaps it would have\nmeant that the upcoming cooling"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 600830.0,
      "end_time": 603980.0,
      "text": "trend would bring\nthe glaciers with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 603980.0,
      "end_time": 607380.0,
      "text": "However, we may have\ndodged a bullet."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 607380.0,
      "end_time": 612040.0,
      "text": "See, the recent eccentricity\nmaximum was a sad little pig,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 612040.0,
      "end_time": 615052.0,
      "text": "and our orbit remains\npretty circular."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 615052.0,
      "end_time": 617820.0,
      "text": "See, as well as the\n100,000-year cycle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 617820.0,
      "end_time": 622530.0,
      "text": "there's a longer 400,000-year\ncycle on top of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 622530.0,
      "end_time": 627540.0,
      "text": "Roughly, every fourth\neccentricity peak is very low."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 627540.0,
      "end_time": 629140.0,
      "text": "That just happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 629140.0,
      "end_time": 631610.0,
      "text": "And the next peak\nwill be weak, also."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 631610.0,
      "end_time": 633085.0,
      "text": "We got lucky."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 633085.0,
      "end_time": 637170.0,
      "text": "We're in a long, stable,\nlow-eccentricity phase."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 637170.0,
      "end_time": 640000.0,
      "text": "Because of this,\nclimate models predict"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 640000.0,
      "end_time": 643450.0,
      "text": "that we have another\n25,000 to 50,000 years"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 643450.0,
      "end_time": 646240.0,
      "text": "of interglacial\nperiod left And that's"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 646240.0,
      "end_time": 650450.0,
      "text": "only if you ignore\nanthropogenic climate change."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 650450.0,
      "end_time": 654340.0,
      "text": "Human influence on the climate\nmesses with the whole equation."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 654340.0,
      "end_time": 657760.0,
      "text": "With CO2 now at 400\nparts per million,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 657760.0,
      "end_time": 662150.0,
      "text": "it's higher than at any point\nin the Quaternary period."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 662150.0,
      "end_time": 664190.0,
      "text": "It's been predicted\nthat this may"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 664190.0,
      "end_time": 668690.0,
      "text": "extent the current\ninterglacial for 100,000 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 668690.0,
      "end_time": 672300.0,
      "text": "So we've probably at least\noffset the next glaciation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 672300.0,
      "end_time": 675330.0,
      "text": "although it wasn't coming\nany time soon, anyway."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 675330.0,
      "end_time": 680010.0,
      "text": "The real question is have we\nended the entire Quaternary ice"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 680010.0,
      "end_time": 681280.0,
      "text": "age?"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 681280.0,
      "end_time": 682540.0,
      "text": "Also possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 682540.0,
      "end_time": 686000.0,
      "text": "However, the recent\nincrease in greenhouse gases"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 686000.0,
      "end_time": 690890.0,
      "text": "is so large and so sudden that\nthere's no precedent anywhere"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 690890.0,
      "end_time": 692440.0,
      "text": "in the climate record."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 692440.0,
      "end_time": 696640.0,
      "text": "This makes modeling our\ninfluence a huge challenge."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 696640.0,
      "end_time": 699710.0,
      "text": "But don't mistake that\nfor a lack of certainty."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 699710.0,
      "end_time": 702730.0,
      "text": "Our influence is\ncertainly enormous."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 702730.0,
      "end_time": 704880.0,
      "text": "There is another\nclimate extreme that's"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 704880.0,
      "end_time": 708690.0,
      "text": "much less fun than a\nlong, mild interglacial."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 708690.0,
      "end_time": 711480.0,
      "text": "That's a sweltering\ngreenhouse climate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 711480.0,
      "end_time": 713460.0,
      "text": "like the one that\ndominated the Mesozoic when"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 713460.0,
      "end_time": 717530.0,
      "text": "the dinosaurs roamed, or Venus."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 717530.0,
      "end_time": 721480.0,
      "text": "See you next week for more\ncold, hard facts on Space Time."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 721480.0,
      "end_time": 724880.0,
      "text": "Last week, we wrapped up our\nconversation on dark energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 724880.0,
      "end_time": 727730.0,
      "text": "talking about anti-gravity,\nnegative pressure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 727730.0,
      "end_time": 729680.0,
      "text": "and conservation of energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 729680.0,
      "end_time": 732240.0,
      "text": "You guys had some\npretty deep comments."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 732240.0,
      "end_time": 736580.0,
      "text": "4798Alexander4798\nasks, is the universe"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 736580.0,
      "end_time": 741800.0,
      "text": "behaving its way because math,\nor is math behaving its way"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 741800.0,
      "end_time": 743780.0,
      "text": "because universe?"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 743780.0,
      "end_time": 744500.0,
      "text": "Whoa."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 744500.0,
      "end_time": 745980.0,
      "text": "Mind blown."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 745980.0,
      "end_time": 748240.0,
      "text": "This is a pretty\nfundamental question."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 748240.0,
      "end_time": 752460.0,
      "text": "My guess-- the universe\ndoesn't know any math."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 752460.0,
      "end_time": 754330.0,
      "text": "It failed pre-calc."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 754330.0,
      "end_time": 757500.0,
      "text": "It wouldn't know a hypotenuse\nif you slapped it with one."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 757500.0,
      "end_time": 760400.0,
      "text": "Mathematics is a model\nthat we use to describe"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 760400.0,
      "end_time": 762370.0,
      "text": "the behavior of the universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 762370.0,
      "end_time": 764040.0,
      "text": "The astonishing\nthing is that it has"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 764040.0,
      "end_time": 766203.0,
      "text": "such incredible\npredictive power."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 766203.0,
      "end_time": 767780.0,
      "text": "Ryan Lidster and\na few others have"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 767780.0,
      "end_time": 770940.0,
      "text": "wondered whether the energy lost\nin the cosmological redshift"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 770940.0,
      "end_time": 775020.0,
      "text": "of photons could account for the\nenergy gained by dark energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 775020.0,
      "end_time": 775520.0,
      "text": "OK."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 775520.0,
      "end_time": 778710.0,
      "text": "So to summarize, as\nthe universe expands,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 778710.0,
      "end_time": 782630.0,
      "text": "the energy in matter in\nany one co-moving volume"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 782630.0,
      "end_time": 785690.0,
      "text": "or expanding volume\nis conserved."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 785690.0,
      "end_time": 789200.0,
      "text": "It gets more spread out, but\nthe method doesn't disappear."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 789200.0,
      "end_time": 793030.0,
      "text": "But photons also get spread\nout and they get red shifted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 793030.0,
      "end_time": 795200.0,
      "text": "so they do lose energy\ninversely proportional"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 795200.0,
      "end_time": 797102.0,
      "text": "to the increasing scale factor."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 797102.0,
      "end_time": 799820.0,
      "text": "Now, Physics Girl has\nan excellent video"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 799820.0,
      "end_time": 801490.0,
      "text": "describing this effect."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 801490.0,
      "end_time": 803130.0,
      "text": "Link in the description."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 803130.0,
      "end_time": 805950.0,
      "text": "So could this lost energy\nbecome dark energy?"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 805950.0,
      "end_time": 806490.0,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 806490.0,
      "end_time": 808310.0,
      "text": "The scales are way off."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 808310.0,
      "end_time": 811080.0,
      "text": "Photons make up only a\ntiny energetic contribution"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 811080.0,
      "end_time": 813450.0,
      "text": "to the modern universe--\nfar less, even,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 813450.0,
      "end_time": 815390.0,
      "text": "than baryonic\nmatter, which itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 815390.0,
      "end_time": 817970.0,
      "text": "is far less than dark energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 817970.0,
      "end_time": 821460.0,
      "text": "The radiation-dominated era\nended around 50,000 years"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 821460.0,
      "end_time": 822950.0,
      "text": "after the Big Bang."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 822950.0,
      "end_time": 825630.0,
      "text": "These days, photons just\ndon't have enough energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 825630.0,
      "end_time": 827680.0,
      "text": "left to contribute."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 827680.0,
      "end_time": 830400.0,
      "text": "Yet dark energy\ncontinues to be created."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 830400.0,
      "end_time": 833600.0,
      "text": "Eugene Khutoransky points\nout that the idea that energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 833600.0,
      "end_time": 836420.0,
      "text": "is not conserved in\nan expanding universe"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 836420.0,
      "end_time": 838280.0,
      "text": "is still pretty speculative."
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 838280.0,
      "end_time": 840504.0,
      "text": "And yeah, there is\nsome speculation here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 840504.0,
      "end_time": 842420.0,
      "text": "but I don't think it's\na speculative statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 842420.0,
      "end_time": 845320.0,
      "text": "to say that the law of\nconservation of energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 845320.0,
      "end_time": 847900.0,
      "text": "as we learned when we\nstudied Newtonian mechanics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 847900.0,
      "end_time": 850400.0,
      "text": "is a feature of flat spacetime."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 850400.0,
      "end_time": 852600.0,
      "text": "Curved spacetime changes things."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 852600.0,
      "end_time": 855730.0,
      "text": "Even gravity from a\nNewtonian perspective"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 855730.0,
      "end_time": 858060.0,
      "text": "requires the invention\nof a new quantity--"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 858060.0,
      "end_time": 860300.0,
      "text": "gravitational potential\nenergy-- in order"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 860300.0,
      "end_time": 863140.0,
      "text": "to preserve energy conservation."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 863140.0,
      "end_time": 865280.0,
      "text": "Described in general\nrelativity, you"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 865280.0,
      "end_time": 867560.0,
      "text": "can still come up with\nconserved quantities--"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 867560.0,
      "end_time": 870070.0,
      "text": "energy analogies\nthat are invariant"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 870070.0,
      "end_time": 872390.0,
      "text": "in, say, an expanding universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 872390.0,
      "end_time": 876530.0,
      "text": "But, for example, a stress\nenergy momentum pseudo tensor"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 876530.0,
      "end_time": 879390.0,
      "text": "isn't mathematically the same\nthing as classical energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 879390.0,
      "end_time": 882460.0,
      "text": "This gets us back to the idea\nof whether the universe knows"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 882460.0,
      "end_time": 883450.0,
      "text": "math."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 883450.0,
      "end_time": 886540.0,
      "text": "The universe is mechanistic\nand its behavior results"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 886540.0,
      "end_time": 889060.0,
      "text": "in emergent\nmathematical laws that"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 889060.0,
      "end_time": 891480.0,
      "text": "allow us to model and\npredict its behavior."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 891480.0,
      "end_time": 893550.0,
      "text": "Conservation of\nenergy is one such law"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 893550.0,
      "end_time": 895450.0,
      "text": "that work in flat space time."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 895450.0,
      "end_time": 897850.0,
      "text": "But energy itself\nis not a thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 897850.0,
      "end_time": 901620.0,
      "text": "We draw energy life bars\nin our animation sometimes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 901620.0,
      "end_time": 905140.0,
      "text": "but the universe doesn't have\nany hidden energy counter."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 905140.0,
      "end_time": 908480.0,
      "text": "It just acts according to\na deep, and presumably very"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 908480.0,
      "end_time": 912090.0,
      "text": "simple, set of fundamental\nrules that give rise"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 912090.0,
      "end_time": 914140.0,
      "text": "to mathematical relationships."
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 914140.0,
      "end_time": 915990.0,
      "text": "And we shouldn't mistake\nthose relationships"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 915990.0,
      "end_time": 918830.0,
      "text": "as themselves being fundamental."
    }
  ]
}